Paul Casey 'desperately' wants to play in the Ryder Cup again . 
  The Englishman left the European Tour in January to concentrate on his game . 
  He has returned to the world's top 50 but is unlikely to rejoin in time to earn qualifying points for the team . 
  Ryder Cup captain Darren Clarke wants Casey on his team for Hazeltine . 
  Casey last played in the 2008 Ryder Cup at Valhalla . 
 